                                        "},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"In terms of "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"a"}],"attrs":{"inline":true}},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"b"}],"attrs":{"inline":true}},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"f(f(x)) - x = x^4 - 2ax^3 + (a^2 - a + 2b)x^2 + (2a^2 - 2ab - 1)x + (b^2 - ab + b)."}],"attrs":{"inline":false}},{"type":"text","text":" At first, this seems like a mess to factor, but suppose we had a root "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"r"}],"attrs":{"inline":true}},{"type":"text","text":" of "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"f(x) - x = 0"}],"attrs":{"inline":true}},{"type":"text","text":". Then we would also have a root of "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"f(f(x)) - x = 0"}],"attrs":{"inline":true}},{"type":"text","text":" since "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"f(r) = r \implies f(f(r)) - r = f(r) - r = 0."}],"attrs":{"inline":false}},{"type":"text","text":" In other words, "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"f(x) - x"}],"attrs":{"inline":true}},{"type":"text","text":" is a factor of "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"f(f(x)) - x"}],"attrs":{"inline":true}},{"type":"text","text":", so for some "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"u"}],"attrs":{"inline":true}},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"v"}],"attrs":{"inline":true}},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"f(f(x)) - x = \big( f(x) - x \big) \big(x^2 + ux + v \big) = \big( x^2 - (a + 1)x + b \big) \big( x^2 + ux + v \big)."}],"attrs":{"inline":false}},{"type":"text","text":" Consider the constant term and the quadratic coefficient in the expansion of "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"f(f(x)) - x"}],"attrs":{"inline":true}},{"type":"text","text":" above. Comparing those values to the factored form of "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"f(f(x)) - x"}],"attrs":{"inline":true}},{"type":"text","text":", we see that we must have "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"bv = b^2 - ab + b, \quad b + v - (a + 1)u = a^2 - a + 2b,"}],"attrs":{"inline":false}},{"type":"text","text":" which we can solve to find "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"v = b - a + 1, \quad u = 1 - a."}],"attrs":{"inline":false}},{"type":"text","text":" Now we are halfway to factoring "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"f(f(x)) - x"}],"attrs":{"inline":true}},{"type":"text","text":": "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"f(f(x)) = \big( x^2 - (a + 1)x + b \big) \big( x^2 + (1 - a)x + (b - a + 1) \big)."}],"attrs":{"inline":false}},{"type":"text","text":" The roots of the two quadratic factors are "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"a + 1 \pm \sqrt{a^2 + 2a - 4b + 1}, \quad a - 1 \pm \sqrt{a^2 + 2a - 4b - 3}."}],"attrs":{"inline":false}},{"type":"text","text":" The roots of "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"f(f(x)) - x = 0"}],"attrs":{"inline":true}},{"type":"text","text":" are integers if and only if the radicands are perfect squares. But the radicands differ by exactly 4, so this is only possible if "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"a^2 + 2a - 4b + 1 = 4, \quad a^2 + 2a - 4b - 3 = 0."}],"attrs":{"inline":false}},{"type":"text","text":" Solving either equation for positive "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"a"}],"attrs":{"inline":true}},{"type":"text","text":" gives the relation we want. The roots of "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"f(f(x)) - x"}],"attrs":{"inline":true}},{"type":"text","text":" are integers exactly when "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"a = -1 + 2\sqrt{b + 1}, \qquad b = n^2 - 1 \geq 3,"}],"attrs":{"inline":false}},{"type":"text","text":" where "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"n"}],"attrs":{"inline":true}},{"type":"text","text":" is an integer. Based on this relation, there are "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\boxed{43}"}],"attrs":{"inline":true}},{"type":"text","text":" pairs "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"(a,b)"}],"attrs":{"inline":true}},{"type":"text","text":" in the desired range."}]},{"type":"text","text":"



